          <section id="GroupC" class="group">
            <h3>Fund Applicant</h3>
            <hr class="post-content-divider clear">
            <div id="GroupCSub1" class="subgroup">
              <h4>Who can apply for a fund?</h4>
              <p>Everyone can apply for a fund, and it's free to apply for one. As long as you think you are who the fund is created for, you can submit your application.</p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div id="GroupCSub2" class="subgroup">
              <h4>How to apply for a fund?</h4>
              <p>On each fund page, you submit your application on the bottom. You have 200 characters to tell the funder why you should get this fund - you can also attach evidence where you see fit.</p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div id="GroupCSub3" class="subgroup">
              <h4>Can I apply to multiple funds at the same time?</h4>
              <p>Yes. As it's free to apply for a fund, applying for multiple funds only gives you more chances to be selected and receive a fund.</p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div id="GroupCSub4" class="subgroup">
              <h4>What to do after being selected for a fund?</h4>
              <p>After you're selected, your application will become a thread where you and the funder can communicate with each other and you can submit updates. When you are done submitting whatever fulfills the completion of the fund, as specified by the funder, you can mark it complete.</p>
            </div>
            <hr>
            <div id="GroupCSub5" class="subgroup">
              <h4>How to receive a fund?</h4>
              <p>After your fund is complete and there is no modification required by the funder, you'll get your fund at the end of the next month. Don't forget to tell us where to send the fund to, on the <a href= '/receiving'>Finances</a> page in your personal folder.</p>
            </div>
